attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, ARM aarch64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt families, designed for AArch64 Linux systems. It features classic IoT botnet characteristics: single-instance enforcement via the lock file '/tmp/.bot_lock', anti-analysis checks for VMware environments, and process enumeration through '/proc' to identify and terminate competing malicious processes. The sample contains a robust suite of DDoS attack implementations, including SYN, ACK, UDP (plain and custom), ICMP, and GRE flooding. It also includes an HTTP attack module ('sub_406984') utilizing a hardcoded Chrome User-Agent string. Command and control (C2) functionality is evidenced by string decryption routines ('sub_4007c0') and a command parser ('sub_4058c0') that handles botnet-specific commands like '!syn', '!ack', and '!udpcustom'.
